    }, `I kept my father company and helped him pass the time, often in front of the shōgi board. Indulging our indolence, we sunk ourselves into the kotatsu, the game board placed over its frame. After each move, we'd retract our hands to the warmth of the quilting. From time to time we'd lose a captured piece, only discovering its absence when we went to start our next game. I can picture still my mother discovering a piece among the ashes and retrieving it with the fire tongs.`), React.createElement(MDXTag, {
