    }, `"The go board is too thick, especially with its feet, for play on the kotatsu. This shōgi board is just right. We can play in comfort. Perfect for a couple of idlers. How 'bout another game?"`), React.createElement(MDXTag, {
      name: "p",
      components: components
    }, `Father would always call for another game after winning. He would call for one after losing too. In short, whether he won or he lost, he was content to settle into the kotatsu and play shōgi. This retirement-like lifestyle was something novel to me, and for a while I embraced its amusements eagerly. As the days and hours passed, though, the energy of youth made me restless for something more. I'd stretch my arms above my head, gripping a shōgi piece, a gold general or a lance, in my fist. Sometimes I'd even yawn overtly.`), React.createElement(MDXTag, {
